\c 26
\p
\v 1
\d Of David.
\q1 Vindicate me, O YHWH, because I have walked in my integrity,\f + Ps 15:2.\f*
\q1 And in YHWH I have trusted, I have not wobbled.\f + Cf. Ps 15:5.\f*
\q1
\v 2 Put me to the test, O YHWH and test me,
\q1 Test my inner being and my heart.
\q1
\v 3 For your steadfast love is before my eyes,
\q1 And I walk in your fidelity.
\q1
\v 4 I do not sit with men of deception,\f + Ps. 24:4; Ps 15:2?; Cf. Ps 1:1.\f*
\q1 And with those who are hidden I have not gone.
\q1
\v 5 I hate the assembly of those who do evil,
\q1 And with the guilty I have not sat.\f + Ps 15:4; cf. Ps 1:1.\f*
\q1
\v 6 I wash my hands in innocence,\f + Ps 24:4.\f*
\q1 And I go around your altar, O YHWH.
\q1
\v 7 To let myself be heard with a voice of praise,
\q1 And to recount all your wonders.
\q1
\v 8 O YHWH I love the dwelling of your house,
\q1 And the dwelling place of your glory.\f + Ps 15:1; 24:3.\f*
\q1
\v 9 Do not gather my life with sinners,
\q1 And with men of blood my life.\f + Ps 24:4?\f*
\q1
\v 10 In whose hands is a plot,
\q1 And their right hand is full of a bribe.\f + Ps 15:5.\f*
\q1
\v 11 But I walk in my integrity,\f + Ps 15:2.\f*
\q1 Redeem me and be gracious to me.
\q1
\v 12 My foot stands on level ground,
\q1 In the assembly I will bless YHWH.\f + Ps 15:1; 24:3?\f*